Misfortune: When a young man, down on his luck, learns about his father's killer's parole, it sets off a cat and mouse chase through the hostile desert, searching for a hidden family inheritance.
2016.  Stars: Desmond Devenish, Xander Bailey, Jenna Kanell

*Review* - "Misfortune" (2016) is an action-packed action crime thriller that involves a lot of revenge, suspense, and car chases with great affection. When a young man comes to know that his father's murderer has been granted parole, he goes on a dangerous cat-and-mouse chase through the inhospitable desert, aiming to uncover a hidden family treasure. Associating the relentless action, crime-incited drama, and surprising turn of events, this gritty film is a real find for all those who are fond of survival thrillers, revenge movies and suspenseful crime films.

Street: Remo Street is a young fighter who comes from a world where nothing is easy, so when he is faced with the opportunity to train with a world class coach, he has to choose between the long hard road to honor and glory, or succumbing to a brutal future as a cage fighter for the Russian Mafia.
2015.  Stars: Quincy Brown, John Hennigan, Mindy Robinson, Mark Ryan

*Review* - "Street" (2015) is an action-packed fight thriller movie that talks about the struggles of Remo Street, a young fighter who do not want to stay in a difficult situation. The guy is offered the opportunity to learn from an international level trainer, he is confronted with the option of taking the easy course to fame or being involved in an illegal cage fight that is controlled by the Russian Mafia. This incredible fight story is not only full of high-octane fight scenes but also has characters that are very emotional and engrossing as well as being stakes drama thriller, for example, that of an underdog. This movie promises an adrenaline-pumping joy ride for those who love movies about MMA, bloodthirsty sport thrillers, and action-packed fighting films.
